{
  "id": "the-mouse-and-the-bull",
  "title": "The Mouse and The Bull",
  "subtitle": "Aesop's Fables, Volume 06",
  "level": "A2-B1",
  "duration": 76.9,
  "audioFileName": "the-mouse-and-the-bull.mp3",
  "sourceURL": "https://librivox.org/aesops-fables-volume-6-fables-126-150/",
  "textSourceURL": "https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/11339",
  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 16.66,
      "end": 20.72,
      "text": "The Mousse and the Bull.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 22.12,
      "end": 25.76,
      "text": "A Bull gave chase to a mouse which had bitten him in the nose.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 25.76,
      "end": 30.04,
      "text": "But the mouse was too quick for him and slipped into a hole in a wall.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 30.64,
      "end": 37.38,
      "text": "The Bull charged furiously into the wall again and again, until he was tired out and sank down on the ground,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 37.38,
      "end": 39.34,
      "text": "exhausted with his efforts.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 40.6,
      "end": 44.4,
      "text": "When all was quiet, the mouse started out and bit him again.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 45.24,
      "end": 51.56,
      "text": "Beside himself with rage, he started to his feet, but by that time the mouse was back in his hole again,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 51.56,
      "end": 55.48,
      "text": "and he could do nothing but bellow and fume and helpless anger.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 56.4,
      "end": 60.04,
      "text": "Presently he heard a shrill little voice say from inside the wall,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 60.7,
      "end": 63.52,
      "text": "you big fellows don't always have it your own way.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 64.18,
      "end": 68.1,
      "text": "You see, sometimes we little ones come off best.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 69.34,
      "end": 72.44,
      "text": "The battle is not always to the strong.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 73.94,
      "end": 76.86,
      "text": "End of the mouse and the bull.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
